# Normalize line endings across platforms (ROADMAP AUD-23).
# Store text as LF in the repo and check it out as LF everywhere — including
# Windows, where core.autocrlf would otherwise rewrite the working tree to CRLF.
# This keeps local `git`, Prettier, and ESLint seeing the same endings the
# Linux CI (the pre-commit gate) enforces.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize line endings or diff as text.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.otf binary

# Note: *.svg is intentionally left as text — it is XML and benefits from LF
# normalization and readable diffs.
